For the most part people was frustrated and annoyed and maybe acted a little out of line.  However, no one has reported to me any such activities which indicates to me they weren't extremely disruptive.  And Im sure my battle field commander would have stepped in if they was extremely disruptive.<br>
<br>
However, I did hear that people made negative comments to a GM.  Now although I'll agree customer service on behalf of Verant truely sucks (and I can give examples), I do not approve of public comments being made.  If you want to tell Verant their decision sucks, please do so privately, or on their message boards.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uhaemish.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Haemish</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ezOP</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(12/4/00 8:26:50 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.godwin.com/sd/haemish.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: character behavior</span><hr size=1> I agree with Zellex wholeheartedly. I've always maintained that these boards should steer clear of personal attacks, and mindless, kneejerk flaming. If there were disruptive individuals on the raid, please email or give their guild leader a /tell, but keep the personal attacks off the boards, please. <br>
<br>
As for Verant Customer Service, I'm firmly in the &quot;IT SUX&quot; camp, but do not believe that public, abusive comments in-game do anything to help the relationship between Verant's CS staff and the player community. Keep it private or keep it silent, but don't make a public spectacle of yourself, especially on CoG raids. <br>
